<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-71-0542 </DOCNO><TEXT>The International Energy Agency's mission is to promote policies thatenable member countries to obtain the energy they need when they needit and as their economies grow. It is concerned with maintaining an emergencysystem for sharing oil supplies in the event of a sudden disruption,with energy conservation, improved energy efficiency, and reduction ofdependence on oil by developing coal, natural gas, nuclear power andrenewable energy sources. The position of nuclear energy is reviewedin the light of the alternatives and public opinion following the Chernobylaccident. Member countries which do not have, or decide to stop using,nuclear energy will have to find technically sound and economically feasiblealternatives. (U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>